article.description: — Adante' Holiman had 21 points in UTSA's 90-80 victory over Incarnate Word on Saturday night.
article.headline: Holiman scores 21 as UTSA knocks off Incarnate Word 90-80
article.linkText: Holiman scores 21 as UTSA knocks off Incarnate Word 90-80
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- — Adante' Holiman had 21 points in UTSA's 90-80 victory over Incarnate Word on Saturday night. Holiman added six rebounds for the Roadrunners (3-4). PJ Carter scored 17 points while shooting 7 for 14, including 2 for 5 from beyond the arc. Carlton Linguard had 16 points and shot 3 for 7 (1 for 3 from 3-point range) and 9 of 12 from the free-throw line. Sky Wicks led the Cardinals (3-3) in scoring, finishing with 24 points, 11 rebounds, five assists and four steals. Josh Morgan added 16 points and two steals for Incarnate Word. Dylan Hayman also had 13 points, two steals and three blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
